{"kind":"textbox","text":"Why FIFO Verification Matters","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Motivation","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"03","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"A FIFO is simple in concept but sensitive at its boundaries: reset, empty, full, read/write overlap, and pointer wrap.","bbox":[72,96,800,56]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Data ordering","bbox":[96,210,276,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Oldest accepted write must be the first valid read. A pointer bug can silently repeat or skip stored data.","bbox":[96,250,276,88]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Flow control","bbox":[96,398,276,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"full and empty are not cosmetic flags. They directly block writes and reads to prevent overflow and underflow.","bbox":[96,438,276,88]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Reset safety","bbox":[454,398,276,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The FIFO must start from a known empty state so later traffic is not contaminated by stale count or pointer values.","bbox":[454,438,276,88]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Debug observability","bbox":[810,398,276,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertions expose internal control mistakes immediately, while the scoreboard checks visible data behavior.","bbox":[810,438,276,88]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Producer","bbox":[528,230,130,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"FIFO\nqueue","bbox":[792,225,80,50]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Consumer","bbox":[1006,230,120,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Why SystemVerilog Over Verilog","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Language choice","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"04","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"SystemVerilog keeps Verilog-style RTL, but adds verification features that are directly useful for this FIFO project.","bbox":[70,92,1020,42]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Verilog HDL","bbox":[100,190,250,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"- Strong fit for synthesizable RTL modeling\n- Modules, nets, registers, always blocks\n- Basic procedural testbenches are possible\n- Limited language support for reusable verification\n- Assertions, classes, coverage, and constrained random are not the core Verilog model","bbox":[100,244,430,214]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"SystemVerilog","bbox":[720,190,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"- Unified design, specification, and verification language\n- Assertions for protocol and temporal properties\n- Classes, mailboxes, and virtual interfaces for testbench reuse\n- Constrained random stimulus and functional coverage support\n- Natural foundation for later UVM migration","bbox":[720,244,430,214]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"IEEE 1800-2023 describes SystemVerilog support for RTL/gate modeling and testbenches using coverage, assertions, object-oriented programming, and constrained random verification.","bbox":[120,580,1040,44]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"OOP Concepts in SystemVerilog","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Basic definitions","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"05","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"SystemVerilog supports object-oriented testbench coding. The idea is to model verification activity as reusable objects instead of only toggling raw signals.","bbox":[70,92,1040,48]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Class","bbox":[92,192,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Blueprint that groups data and tasks/functions.","bbox":[92,226,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"class transaction; ... endclass","bbox":[92,268,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Object","bbox":[482,192,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Runtime instance created from a class.","bbox":[482,226,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"transaction tr = new();","bbox":[482,268,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Encapsulation","bbox":[872,192,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Keep related fields and behavior in one unit.","bbox":[872,226,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"transaction stores wr_en, rd_en, data, flags","bbox":[872,268,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Abstraction","bbox":[92,370,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Use a simple method call while hiding internal steps.","bbox":[92,404,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"env.run(); driver.run();","bbox":[92,446,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Inheritance","bbox":[482,370,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Create a child class from a parent class.","bbox":[482,404,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"class child extends parent;","bbox":[482,446,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Polymorphism","bbox":[872,370,142,26]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Base handle can call child-specific behavior.","bbox":[872,404,292,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"virtual function / task","bbox":[872,446,292,22]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"For this project, the most visible OOP features are classes, objects, encapsulation, abstraction, mailboxes, randomization, and virtual interfaces.","bbox":[114,568,1030,42]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"How OOP Appears in This Testbench","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Project mapping","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"06","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Your SystemVerilog testbench uses objects to represent FIFO operations and verification components.","bbox":[70,92,1040,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"transaction","bbox":[74,191,168,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Object for one FIFO operation\nrand oper, rand wr_data\nconstraints control stimulus","bbox":[74,226,168,62]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"generator","bbox":[316,191,168,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Creates transaction objects\nrandomizes them\nsends using mailbox","bbox":[316,226,168,62]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"driver","bbox":[558,191,168,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Gets transaction from mailbox\ncalls write() or read()\ndrives virtual fifo_if","bbox":[558,226,168,62]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"monitor","bbox":[800,191,168,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Samples DUT interface\ncreates observed transaction\nsends to scoreboard","bbox":[800,226,168,62]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"scoreboard","bbox":[1042,191,168,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Stores expected queue\ncompares rd_data\ncounts mismatches","bbox":[1042,226,168,62]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"environment class","bbox":[110,394,210,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Creates and connects the component objects:\ngen = new(gdmbx);\ndrv = new(gdmbx);\nmon = new(msmbx);\nsco = new(msmbx);","bbox":[110,430,430,80]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Benefit to testing","bbox":[700,394,210,24]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"- Cleaner separation of stimulus, driving, monitoring, and checking\n- Randomized transactions create many read/write cases\n- Mailboxes decouple components and make data flow clear\n- Same structure can be migrated naturally toward UVM","bbox":[700,430,430,80]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Short viva line: SystemVerilog OOP turns the testbench into reusable verification components instead of a single block of procedural signal toggling.","bbox":[116,582,1030,36]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Synchronous FIFO Basics","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"DUT behavior","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"07","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"First-in first-out rule","bbox":[70,98,400,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The FIFO accepts writes into the tail and reads from the head. Status flags are generated from occupancy count.","bbox":[70,132,800,32]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Write side","bbox":[122,214,196,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"wr_en\nwr_data\nwr_ptr advances","bbox":[124,250,192,54]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"FIFO storage","bbox":[530,198,220,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"oldest data at front\nfifo_count tracks occupancy\nfull / empty from count","bbox":[532,242,220,74]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Read side","bbox":[962,214,196,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"rd_en\nrd_data\nrd_ptr advances","bbox":[964,250,192,54]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Key control equations","bbox":[196,454,366,18]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"do_write = wr_en && !full;\ndo_read  = rd_en && !empty;\nfull     = (fifo_count == DEPTH);\nempty    = (fifo_count == 0);","bbox":[196,478,366,82]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Project parameters","bbox":[682,450,346,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"DW = 8 data bits\nAW = 4 address bits\nDEPTH = 2^AW = 16 entries\nfifo_count range = 0..16","bbox":[682,490,346,74]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Design Under Test Architecture","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"sync_fifo_ram + sync_ram","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"08","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The verified DUT separates control from storage: sync_fifo_ram manages pointers/count/flags, while sync_ram stores data.","bbox":[70,92,1050,44]}
