{"kind":"textbox","text":"Key Findings and Contribution","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"What the project demonstrates","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"18","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The project demonstrates that assertion-based verification improves observability beyond transaction-level checking alone.","bbox":[70,92,1050,44]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"1. Assertions localize failures","bbox":[102,196,300,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Internal signals such as wr_ptr, rd_ptr, fifo_count, do_write, and do_read are checked at the clock where the rule is violated.","bbox":[102,236,300,104]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"2. Scoreboard validates behavior","bbox":[492,196,300,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The queue-based reference model confirms whether the output data still follows FIFO order after control faults.","bbox":[492,236,300,104]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"3. Waveforms explain timing","bbox":[882,196,300,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"EPWave evidence connects assertion timestamps to signal transitions, making root cause analysis clear.","bbox":[882,236,300,104]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Main contribution","bbox":[160,454,240,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"A parameterized synchronous FIFO was verified with a SystemVerilog class-based environment, bound SVA checker, scoreboard, and five intentional negative tests. The result is a reusable verification base that can be extended toward UVM.","bbox":[160,492,920,46]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Conclusion, Future Work, and References","bbox":[52,18,940,34]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Close","bbox":[925,19,300,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Assertion-Based Verification of Synchronous FIFO","bbox":[52,684,600,20]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"19","bbox":[1168,678,58,30]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Conclusion","bbox":[94,120,496,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"The clean FIFO behavior was established first. Each injected RTL fault produced assertion or scoreboard failures, proving that the environment can detect reset, boundary, flag, pointer, and data-order bugs.","bbox":[94,160,496,96]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Future improvements","bbox":[694,120,496,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"Migrate to UVM agents and sequences.\nAdd functional coverage bins for full/empty transitions.\nAdd constrained random regression tests.\nAdd coverage-driven closure and CI simulation scripts.","bbox":[694,160,496,96]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"References","bbox":[100,344,220,28]}
{"kind":"textbox","text":"1. IEEE SA, IEEE 1800-2023: SystemVerilog - Unified Hardware Design, Specification, and Verification Language.\n2. Accellera, Universal Verification Methodology community and standards pages.\n3. Local project report: TIET_Assertion_Based_FIFO_Verification_Report.docx.\n4. Project source files: rtl/sync_fifo_ram.sv, rtl/sync_ram.sv, tb/assert_fifo_ram.sv, tb/*.svh.\n5. Simulation evidence: EPWave and transcript screenshots from images/issue1 through images/issue5.","bbox":[100,392,1000,114]}
